org.raistlic.common.config.entity

Annotation Type ConfigConstructor


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={CONSTRUCTOR,METHOD})
public @interface ConfigConstructor
    The annotation is to mark a static factory method or constructor that is preferred to be used as the method to create a config entity instance. The annotated static factory method or constructor must have all its parameters marked with ConfigProperty, unless no parameters needed. Although not restricted, it is preferred that only one of the static factory methods and constructors being marked as ConfigConstructor, or otherwise which one to be used is undefined.
